oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Harper family home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Harriette Harper's (1852-1943) home. Harriett was the daughter of Ralph McKinney and Mary (Carter) McKinney, and was the widow of Haskell T. Harper (1847-1911). Four people and a horse-drawn buggy are posed in front of the house. The young girl is holding a doll.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Carriages & coaches
